<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910221-0159</DOCNO><DOCID>910221-0159.</DOCID><HL>   Nelson Holdings' Deadline</HL><DATE>02/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   NNH T.NNH</CO><IN>RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   NHI Nelson Holdings International Ltd. said the deadlinefor a definitive agreement to sell its Nelson EntertainmentGroup to New York financier Stephen C. Swid has been extendedone week to Feb. 26.   The extension is the second from the original deadline ofFeb. 4. Last December, Mr. Swid, who is chairman and chiefexecutive officer of SCS Communications Inc., signed a letterof intent to buy the independent movie company for $30million in cash and notes and the assumption of $186 millionin debt.</LP><TEXT>   The company said the extension will provide additionaltime for negotiations and documentation and to pursuenecessary consents from its bank and others. Toronto-basedNelson Holdings owns Nelson Entertainment Group and a 69%stake in Nelson Vending Technology Ltd. Like many otherindependents, Nelson has fallen on hard times and has soughtan investor to bail it out.</TEXT></DOC>